    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/419a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-15T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1704. B–170. For Boyden’s<note n="1" xml:id="d2fn1">Roland W. Boyden, American
                        unofficial representative on the Reparation Commission.</note> personal
                    information. Department has practically decided upon full withdrawal of
                    participation by United States on Reparation Commission as well as on other
                    commissions in Europe. If you have opinions and suggestions for best carrying
                    out such decision, Department invites you to send them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
